Montague Harry Holcroft (14 May 1902 Rangiora - 24 September 1993 Rangiora) was a New Zealand essayist, and novelist.[1] He wrote for the Southland Times, beginning in 1936. He edited the New Zealand Listener, starting in 1949.[2] He helped found the New Zealand branch of UNESCO.[3]
